column1: ERA5Wind indicates mean winds taken from the purple box (Table 1) to calculate alongshore winds. Spd (Wind speed), U (vector positive to the east), V (positive to north), Deg (degree heading). SW at the end of the name indicates alongshore wind vectors that have been reoriented to make V pointing toward 242 degrees. Pit indicates winds averaged from the orange box to identify piteraq events. Bar indicates winds averaged from the yellow box to identify barrier wind events. Stress indicates wind stress from the purple box area. Tempshelf indicates ocean mooring temperatures measured on the continental shelf, Tempmid indicates temperatures taken from within the fjord. Both show the depths at which the temperatures were taken. SSH is sea surface heights from Harden et al. (2014).
